Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, Lisa Monaco, met with her British and French counterparts to discuss counterterrorism cooperation, the status of the campaign against ISIL, and the threat of terrorist use of weapons of mass destruction. Monaco emphasized the close partnership and shared goals between the United States, Britain, and France in pressuring terrorist groups that threaten Western interests. The officials also reviewed collective efforts to address the terrorist threat in Iraq, Syria, Libya, and the Sahel, and expressed their determination to defeat ISIL.